.TH CLAMBBACK 1 "Jul 2026" "version 1.0.0-alpha.2"
.SH NAME
clambback \- configurable TLS transport service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clambback
[\fB\-htv\fR] [\fB\-l\fR \fILOG\fR] [\fB\-k\fR \fIKEYLOG\fR] [[\fB\-c\fR] \fICONFIG\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clambback
loads a JSON configuration file and starts the selected client, forward, nat, or server mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c, " " \-\-config=\fICONFIG\fR
Set the config file to be loaded. Default is \fI/etc/clambback/config.json\fR unless changed at build time.
.TP
.BR \-h, " " \-\-help
Print help message.
.TP
.BR \-k, " " \-\-keylog=\fIKEYLOG\fR
Set the keylog file to be written.
.TP
.BR \-l, " " \-\-log=\fILOG\fR
Set the log file to be written. If not specified, the log is written to stderr.
.TP
.BR \-t, " " \-\-test
Test the config file without starting the service.
.TP
.BR \-v, " " \-\-version
Print version and build info.
.SH FILES
.TP
.IR /etc/clambback/config.json
The default config file for system installations.
